  plantName: Oak Tree
  description: An oak is a hardwood tree or shrub in the genus Quercus (beech family),
    featuring lobed leaves, woody-cupped acorns, and durable timber. With around
    450 species, they are long-lived keystone species, supporting diverse wildlife
    and ecosystems. They are widely used for timber, landscaping, and shade, thriving
    in the Northern Hemisphere.
